# =============================================================================
# .dockerignore — keep the build context small + force a clean install
# =============================================================================
# Everything node_modules / build-output related must come from the deps and
# builder stages, not the host. Otherwise a stale Windows-built node_modules
# can poison the Linux container (postgres bindings, esbuild platform bins…).

# --- dependencies, build output, caches ---
**/node_modules
**/.next
**/.turbo
**/dist
**/coverage
**/.cache
**/.pnpm-store

# --- VCS, IDEs, OS ---
.git
.gitignore
.gitattributes
.github
.vscode
.idea
**/.DS_Store
**/Thumbs.db

# --- env files (NEVER bake secrets into the image) ---
.env
.env.*
!.env.example
**/.env
**/.env.*
!**/.env.example

# --- docker bits themselves ---
compose.yaml
docker-compose*.yaml
**/Dockerfile
**/.dockerignore

# --- design assets / reference mocks not used at runtime ---
Reference_Folder
**/*.psd
**/*.fig

# --- logs / tmp ---
**/*.log
**/tmp
**/.tmp

# --- test artefacts ---
**/test-results
**/playwright-report
